XYZ Workshop began in early 2013, with the aim of making 3D printing accessible to the everyday person from designers, to kids, and mums. The vision was to allow anyone to enjoy that extra level of customisation and call something their own as a departure from the world of mass production that we live in.

XYZ Workshop is a creative hub for collaboration between different creative enterprises and a teaching platform for 3D printing technology to different interested groups, be it school kids or a person just interested in making his own Iphone case. We will be working with designers to show case their unique designs, to push the boundaries of desktop 3d printing.

All items are licensed as public domain, you can sell anything I post up, preferably with attribution. But I'm not going to try and stop anyone who sells one of my items without my knowledge or crediting me, I'm honestly OK with that.
